Maryk was in full command.        
 The entire ship was               
 obeying his orders.

310
00:15:29.887 --> 00:15:32.389
I thought that.                   
 for the safety of the ship.

311
00:15:32.431 --> 00:15:34.808
my best course was                
 to obey his orders.

312
00:15:34.850 --> 00:15:36.810
Mr. Keefer. were you 
              aboard the   Caine

313
00:15:36.852 --> 00:15:39.313
throughout the period     
          that Captain Queeg        
          was in command?

314
00:15:39.355 --> 00:15:43.067
Yes. I was.                       
      Did you ever observe any      
      evidence of insanity in him?

315
00:15:43.108 --> 00:15:45.736
I don't--                         
 I can't answer that question.     
 not being a psychiatrist.

316
00:15:45.778 --> 00:15:47.863
Did you ever think        
          he might be insane?

317
00:15:47.905 --> 00:15:49.782
Objection.

318
00:15:49.823 --> 00:15:53.118
Witness is not an expert      
      and matters of opinion        
      are not admissible evidence.

319
00:15:53.160 --> 00:15:54.703
I withdraw the question.

320
00:15:54.745 --> 00:15:58.123
Mr. Keefer.               
          at any time prior         
          to December 18th.

321
00:15:58.165 --> 00:16:01.543
were you informed             
      that Maryk suspected Queeg    
      of being mentally ill?

322
00:16:01.585 --> 00:16:04.296
Yes. I was.                   
          Describe                  
          how you learned this.

323
00:16:04.338 --> 00:16:05.756
Well. uh. let me see.

324
00:16:05.798 --> 00:16:08.509
Two-- Two weeks                   
 before the cyclone.

325
00:16:08.550 --> 00:16:10.594
Maryk showed me                   
 a medical log

326
00:16:10.636 --> 00:16:13.222
