 from a damaged aircraft.

519
00:24:39.269 --> 00:24:40.937
I see.

520
00:24:40.979 --> 00:24:44.191
Did you have a chance     
          to practice much law?     
 A little. sir.

521
00:24:45.609 --> 00:24:46.651
[sighs]

522
00:24:46.693 --> 00:24:48.445
Lieutenant Maryk.

523
00:24:48.487 --> 00:24:50.489
Yes. sir.

524
00:24:50.530 --> 00:24:52.908
I need to know if you're      
      happy with your counsel's     
      conduct of the defense.

525
00:24:52.949 --> 00:24:55.494
Sir. if he answers                
 that question.                    
 he does on blind faith.

526
00:24:55.535 --> 00:24:57.954
Can I just have a moment          
 to speak to my client privately?

527
00:24:57.996 --> 00:25:00.248
[sighs]

528
00:25:00.957 --> 00:25:02.083
Two minutes.

529
00:25:02.125 --> 00:25:03.502
[Greenwald]   
                      Come on.

530
00:25:03.960 --> 00:25:05.337
Thank you.

531
00:25:07.130 --> 00:25:09.424
So. do you want           
          to get rid of me?

532
00:25:10.467 --> 00:25:11.968
I don't know.

533
00:25:13.053 --> 00:25:15.347
I think I'm screwed               
 at this point.

534
00:25:15.388 --> 00:25:17.349
Fifteen years                     
 in the brig?

535
00:25:17.390 --> 00:25:19.184
Mm-hmm.

536
00:25:20.727 --> 00:25:23.522
Tell me one thing.                
 Why didn't you                    
 cross-examine Tom?

537
00:25:23.563 --> 00:25:25.857
I don't have time         
          to tell you everything.

538
00:25:25.899 --> 00:25:28.568
Tom Keefer knows everything       
 the captain did. Everything.      
              I'm sure he does.

539
00:25:28.610 --> 00:25:30.487
If he wouldn't talk.              
 it's up to you                    
 to drag it out.

540
00:25:30.529 --> 00:25:32.614
Wasn't it?                        
          You don't understand.

541
00:25:32.656 --> 00:25:34.407
No. I don't understand            
 what you're doing.                
 That's for sure.

542
00:25:34.449 --> 00:25:35.909
I want to fight           
          this case.                
 Why?

543
00:25:35.951 --> 00:25:37.619
Because                   
          I want to win it.         
      Why?

544
00:25:37.661 --> 00:25:39.538
Is that not enough?

545
00:25:39.579 --> 00:25:41.248
Before you said you'd             
 rather be prosecuting             
 than defending me.

546
00:25:41.289 --> 00:25:42.999
So maybe this is                  
 your bizarre way                  
 of prosecuting.

547
00:25:43.041 --> 00:25:46.169
Steve. listen to me   
              very carefully.

548
00:25:46.211 --> 00:25:48.964
Implicating Keefer        
          harms you.                
      What?

549
00:25:49.005 --> 00:25:52.342
Two disgruntled bastards      
      instead of one heroic exec.

550
00:25:52.384 --> 00:25:55.637
I have a chance           
          with one heroic exec.

551
00:25:55.679 --> 00:25:58.974
Making that stick     
              is the only chance    
              for you to win.

552
00:26:05.063 --> 00:26:07.524
For the record.                   
 the court asks the accused.

553
00:26:07.566 --> 00:26:09.985
are you satisfied             
      with your counsel?

554
00:26:11.653 --> 00:26:13.530
I'm satisfied. sir.

555
00:26:13.572 --> 00:26:16.408
Court will not            
          reopen this question.     
 I understand that. sir.

556
00:26:16.449 --> 00:26:19.077
I'm satisfied                 
      with Lieutenant Greenwald.

557
00:26:19.119 --> 00:26:21.705
Proceed with your case.   
          Commander Challee.

558
00:26:22.664 --> 00:26:24.249
Call Lieutenant Keith.

559
00:26:33.466 --> 00:26:35.427
State your name. rank             
 and present station.

560
00:26:35.468 --> 00:26:38.555
Willis Keith.             
          US Navy Junior Grade.

561
00:26:38.597 --> 00:26:40.682
assistant communications officer 
 on the USS   Caine.

562
00:26:40.724 --> 00:26:43.184
Mr. Keith. were you               
 officer of the deck of the   Caine

563
00:26:43.226 --> 00:26:45.395
on December 18th. 2022?

564
00:26:45.437 --> 00:26:46.813
I was.

565
00:26:46.855 --> 00:26:49.524
Was the captain relieved      
      of his command on that date?

566
00:26:49.566 --> 00:26:50.609
Yes. ma'am.

567
00:26:50.650 --> 00:26:52.193
Do you know why           
          the executive officer

568
00:26:52.235 --> 00:26:53.612
relieved the captain?     
 Yes.

569
00:26:53.653 --> 00:26:56.740
Captain Queeg                 
      had lost control of himself

570
00:26:56.781 --> 00:26:59.534
and the ship              
          was in grave danger       
          of foundering.

571
00:27:00.619 --> 00:27:02.203
How many years            
          have you served at sea.   
          Lieutenant?

572
00:27:02.245 --> 00:27:04.164
One year. three months.

573
00:27:04.205 --> 00:27:06.207
Do you know how many years    
      Commander Queeg               
      has served at sea?

574
00:27:06.249 --> 00:27:08.168
I guess about 17 years.

575
00:27:08.209 --> 00:27:10.128
Which one of you is           
      better qualified to judge

576
00:27:10.170 --> 00:27:12.714
whether a ship            
          is foundering or not?

577
00:27:12.756 --> 00:27:14.758
Myself. ma'am.

578
00:27:14.799 --> 00:27:17.344
if I'm in possession          
      of my faculties               
      and Commander Queeg isn't.

579
00:27:17.385 --> 00:27:19.220
Well. what makes you think        
 he wasn't in possession           
 of his faculties?

580
00:27:19.262 --> 00:27:21.473
He wasn't on the morning 
          of December 18th.

581
00:27:21.514 --> 00:27:24.643
Oh. Have you studied      
          medicine or psychiatry?   
 No.

582
00:27:24.684 --> 00:27:29.105
Did the captain foam or rave 
      or make insane gestures?

583
00:27:29.147 --> 00:27:32.901
No. No.                           
 What he did do was just as bad.

584
00:27:32.942 --> 00:27:34.069
Clarify that. will you?

585
00:27:34.110 --> 00:27:36.321
His orders were vague.

586
00:27:36.363 --> 00:27:39.783
He insisted on going south        
 when we had a north wind          
 of 90 miles an hour behind us.

587
00:27:39.824 --> 00:27:42.535
With a stern wind that strong.    
 the ship couldn't be controlled.

588
00:27:42.577 --> 00:27:45.705
In your expert opinion        
      as ship handler. that is.

589
00:27:45.747 --> 00:27:49.125
Well. Steve Maryk thought so.     
 and he's an expert ship handler.

590
00:27:49.167 --> 00:27:53.797
Were you completely loyal     
      to your captain or not.       
      prior to 18 December?

591
00:27:53.838 --> 00:27:58.635
I was. uh. antagonistic       
      to Captain Queeg              
      at certain isolated times.

592
00:27:58.677 --> 00:28:00.679
At what isolated times    
          were you antagonistic?

593
00:28:00.720 --> 00:28:03.098
When the captain          
          mistreated his men.       
          I opposed him.

594
00:28:03.139 --> 00:28:04.808
When did the captain      
          ever mistreat his men?

595
00:28:04.849 --> 00:28:07.936
Well. for one thing.              
 he systematically persecuted

596
00:28:07.977 --> 00:28:09.854
Gunners Mate Second Class         
 Stilwell.

597
00:28:09.896 --> 00:28:11.981
In what way?

598
00:28:12.023 --> 00:28:15.068
First. he restricted him      
      to the ship for six months    
      for reading on watch.

599
00:28:15.110 --> 00:28:17.987
Refused to grant him leave        
 when we were back in the States   
 in December 2021.

600
00:28:18.029 --> 00:28:22.867
The man was getting           
      anonymous messages about      
      his wife's infidelity.

601
00:28:22.909 --> 00:28:26.037
[stammers. sighs]             
      Maryk gave Stilwell           
      a 72-hour emergency leave.

602
00:28:26.079 --> 00:28:27.872
He returned a few hours       
      over leave--

603
00:28:27.914 --> 00:28:31.793
Hold on. Hold on.         
          You say that Maryk        
          gave Stilwell leave.

604
00:28:33.503 --> 00:28:35.922
Did Maryk know that the captain   
 had denied Stilwell leave?

605
00:28:35.964 --> 00:28:37.799
Yes.

606
00:28:37.841 --> 00:28:41.177
Did Maryk check with the captain 
 before authorizing this leave?

607
00:28:41.219 --> 00:28:43.138
No. um...

608
00:28:43.179 --> 00:28:45.640
Are you testifying.   
              Mr. Keith.

609
00:28:45.682 --> 00:28:48.852
that Maryk                
          deliberately violated     
          his captain's orders?

610
00:28:50.937 --> 00:28:52.355
Uh...

611
00:28:53.732 --> 00:28:57.694
I-- I mean.                   
      i-it was my fault. actually.

612
00:28:57.736 --> 00:28:59.696
'Cause I begged him to.   
          He was--

613
00:28:59.738 --> 00:29:01.990
Mr. Keith. we now             
      have your testimony

614
00:29:02.031 --> 00:29:03.992
that you and Stilwell     
          and Maryk

615
00:29:04.033 --> 00:29:06.870
conspired to circumvent   
          an express order by       
          your commanding officer

616
00:29:06.911 --> 00:29:10.331
a whole year          
              before the cyclone    
              of 18 December.

617
00:29:10.373 --> 00:29:12.834
Now. please tell the court

618
00:29:12.876 --> 00:29:16.588
any other instances       
          of mistreatment           
          that occur to you.

619
00:29:18.214 --> 00:29:20.091
He cut off Internet access    
      for six months

620
00:29:20.133 --> 00:29:22.802
'cause he wasn't invited      
      to a screening by mistake.

621
00:29:22.844 --> 00:29:26.055
Uh. he restricted water use   
      in the middle of a heat wave

622
00:29:26.097 --> 00:29:29.267
'cause he said the men            
 were using too much.              
 they had to be taught a lesson.

623
00:29:29.309 --> 00:29:34.355
Did the captain ever issue        
 any rules or punishments          
 not permitted by regulations?

624
00:29:35.565 --> 00:29:38.109
He never did anything         
      not allowed by regulations.

625
00:29:38.151 --> 00:29:40.528
You don't like the captain.   
      do you. Lieutenant?

626
00:29:40.570 --> 00:29:42.489
Oh. I did.        
                  I did at first.

627
00:29:42.530 --> 00:29:44.240
Very much.                        
                          Mm-hmm.

628
00:29:44.282 --> 00:29:46.993
But I gradually       
              came to realize

629
00:29:47.035 --> 00:29:49.746
that he was a petty tyrant    
      and utterly incompetent.

630
00:29:49.788 --> 00:29:52.207
Did you think         
              he was insane. too?

631
00:29:52.248 --> 00:29:54.250
Not until the day     
              of the cyclone.

632
00:29:54.292 --> 00:29:57.045
Very well.                        
 Come to the day of the storm.

633
00:29:57.086 --> 00:29:58.922
Was your decision     
              to obey Maryk

634
00:29:58.963 --> 00:30:01.591
based on your judgment that   
      the captain had gone mad?

635
00:30:01.633 --> 00:30:04.803
Or was it based           
          on your hatred            
          of Captain Queeg?

636
00:30:06.429 --> 00:30:11.476
I-- I just-- I don't remember     
 my state of mind at that time.

637
00:30:12.143 --> 00:30:13.728
No further questions.

638
00:30:13.770 --> 00:30:16.898
Mr. Keith. you stated             
 you disliked Captain Queeg. yes?

639
00:30:16.940 --> 00:30:18.900
I did dislike him.

640
00:30:18.942 --> 00:30:21.653
And did you state all             
 your reasons for disliking him?   
              Not at all.

641
00:30:21.694 --> 00:30:24.239
Okay. well. please.               
 state the rest                    
 of those reasons now.

642
00:30:24.280 --> 00:30:27.242
Well. for one thing.          
      he extorted                   
      a thousand bucks from me.

643
00:30:27.283 --> 00:30:29.327
Objection.

644
00:30:29.369 --> 00:30:31.955
The issue in this case            
 is not whether Captain Queeg      
 was a model officer.

645
00:30:31.996 --> 00:30:33.832
but whether he was insane         
 on 18 December.

646
00:30:33.873 --> 00:30:35.959
Defense counsel hasn't            
 even touched that issue.

647
00:30:36.000 --> 00:30:38.503
Well. please the court.           
 this bears directly               
 on the fitness

648
00:30:38.545 --> 00:30:40.672
of Captain Queeg                  
 to command a naval vessel.

649
00:30:40.713 --> 00:30:43.049
And as evidence.                  
 it is nothing but clarification

650
00:30:43.091 --> 00:30:45.385
of Keith's dislike                
 for his commanding officer.

651
00:30:45.426 --> 00:30:49.347
a fact brought out                
 by trial counsel.                 
 at great pains. I might add.

652
00:30:49.389 --> 00:30:51.933
under direct examination.

653
00:30:53.393 --> 00:30:55.019
The objection is overruled.

654
00:30:56.563 --> 00:31:00.733
Mr. Keith.                        
 could you please describe         
 this so-called extortion?

655
00:31:00.775 --> 00:31:04.571
Well. this was back           
      last December                 
      in Port Doha. Qatar.

656
00:31:04.612 --> 00:31:07.740
Uh. the captain had this crate.

657
00:31:07.782 --> 00:31:11.035
this big crate                    
 full of duty-free whiskey         
 that he wanted to sneak aboard.

658
00:31:11.077 --> 00:31:12.871
He appointed me boat officer.

659
00:31:12.912 --> 00:31:15.665
and a working party started       
 to load the crate in the gig.

660
00:31:15.707 --> 00:31:17.876
It was incredibly heavy.

661
00:31:17.917 --> 00:31:22.505
and Captain Queeg...              
 got excited

662
00:31:22.547 --> 00:31:25.800
and started screaming out         
 a whole bunch                     
 of contradictory orders.

663
00:31:25.842 --> 00:31:28.136
Sailors got rattled.              
 they dropped the crate            
 in the water.

664
00:31:28.177 --> 00:31:31.556
it sank like a stone.             
 I was out a thousand bucks.

665
00:31:31.598 --> 00:31:33.641
No. you mean the captain      
      was out a thousand bucks.

666
00:31:33.683 --> 00:31:36.019
No. no. no. sir.                  
 I was.

667
00:31:36.060 --> 00:31:38.187
Captain informed me               
 it was my responsibility.

668
00:31:38.229 --> 00:31:40.398
'cause I was boat officer         
 in charge of loading.

669
00:31:40.440 --> 00:31:43.568
and he asked me                   
 what I wanted to do about it.

670
00:31:43.610 --> 00:31:45.236
I was supposed to go              
 on leave the next day.

671
00:31:45.278 --> 00:31:48.573
My girlfriend had flown out       
 from New York to be with me.

672
00:31:48.615 --> 00:31:50.366
so I went to the captain.

673
00:31:50.408 --> 00:31:53.578
I apologized for my stupidity.

674
00:31:53.620 --> 00:31:56.205
and I offered to pay              
 for the crate.

675
00:31:56.247 --> 00:31:59.709
He took my money                  
 and signed my leave papers.

676
00:32:00.960 --> 00:32:03.755
What other reasons do you have    
 for disliking Captain Queeg?

677
00:32:03.796 --> 00:32:05.465
Well. my chief reason             
 for disliking Captain Queeg

678
00:32:05.506 --> 00:32:07.759
was his cowardice                 
 in dangerous situations.

679
00:32:07.800 --> 00:32:08.760
Objection!

680
00:32:08.801 --> 00:32:10.011
Counsel                       
      is originating evidence

681
00:32:10.053 --> 00:32:12.305
beyond the scope              
      of direct examination.

682
00:32:12.347 --> 00:32:16.017
He is leading the witness     
      to irresponsible libel        
      of an officer of the Navy.

683
00:32:16.059 --> 00:32:18.895
Please the court.                 
 the witness's dislike             
 of Captain Queeg

684
00:32:18.937 --> 00:32:21.397
was not only in the scope         
 of direct examination.

685
00:32:21.439 --> 00:32:23.733
it was the key fact               
 brought out.

686
00:32:23.775 --> 00:32:27.779
Now. the witness has confessed    
 an ignorance of psychiatry.

687
00:32:28.571 --> 00:32:30.198
Things Captain Queeg did

688
00:32:30.239 --> 00:32:33.284
which forced the witness          
 in his ignorance                  
 to dislike him

689
00:32:33.326 --> 00:32:36.079
may in fact have been             
 the helpless acts                 
 of a sick man.

690
00:32:36.120 --> 00:32:39.207
I respectfully                
