Sir. everything               
      was happening very fast.

1680
01:18:30.872 --> 01:18:33.375
We had to mark the area           
 and then get out of there

1681
01:18:33.417 --> 01:18:36.336
and make room for other ships     
 to come into the area.            
 as I said.

1682
01:18:36.378 --> 01:18:39.089
These are your factual            
 recollections. Commander?

1683
01:18:39.131 --> 01:18:41.383
Those are the facts. sir.

1684
01:18:43.051 --> 01:18:44.428
Resume your examination.

1685
01:18:44.469 --> 01:18:46.096
Commander.                        
 did you make it a practice

1686
01:18:46.138 --> 01:18:48.807
to retire to your room            
 during minesweeping operations?

1687
01:18:48.849 --> 01:18:51.727
Well. that's                  
      an insulting question.        
      The answer is no.

1688
01:18:51.768 --> 01:18:54.104
I had to be on                
      every side of that bridge     
      at all times.

1689
01:18:54.146 --> 01:18:59.025
I-I had Maryk as a navigator      
 and Keith as an officer of        
 the deck at general quarters.

1690
01:18:59.067 --> 01:19:01.737
Invariably. they'd squirrel   
      over to the same side         
      of the bridge

1691
01:19:01.778 --> 01:19:05.157
and I'd have to be captain.       
 navigator and officer of          
 the deck all rolled up into one.

1692
01:19:05.198 --> 01:19:07.951
That's why I had to go        
      from one side of the bridge   
      to the other all the time.

1693
01:19:07.993 --> 01:19:10.162
And that's the truth.

1694
01:19:10.203 --> 01:19:12.748
I don't care how many damn lies   
 have been told about me           
 in this courtroom.

1695
01:19:12.789 --> 01:19:14.958
The court                     
      will question the witness.

1696
01:19:15.000 --> 01:19:18.837
Sir. the witness                  
 is obviously and understandably   
 agitated by this ordeal

1697
01:19:18.879 --> 01:19:21.590
and I request a recess    
          to give him               
          a breathing space.

1698
01:19:21.631 --> 01:19:23.884
I'm not agitated              
      in the least.

1699
01:19:23.925 --> 01:19:26.094
I'm glad to answer            
      any and all questions.

1700
01:19:26.136 --> 01:19:28.054
[marbles clacking]

1701
01:19:28.096 --> 01:19:31.099
In fact.                          
 I-I demand the opportunity        
 to set the record straight

1702
01:19:31.141 --> 01:19:35.645
for any derogatory statements     
 made about me in testimony        
 that's gone before.

1703
01:19:35.687 --> 01:19:39.232
I didn't make a single mistake    
 in the 15 months                  
 I was aboard the   Caine.

1704
01:19:39.274 --> 01:19:41.193
and I-I can prove it.

1705
01:19:41.234 --> 01:19:43.528
I've had a spotless record        
 up until now

1706
01:19:43.570 --> 01:19:45.655
and I don't want it   
              being discredited

1707
01:19:45.697 --> 01:19:49.451
by these lies and distortions     
 told by these disloyal officers.

1708
01:19:49.493 --> 01:19:52.662
Commander.                    
      would you like a recess?

1709
01:19:52.704 --> 01:19:53.747
Certainly not.

1710
01:19:53.789 --> 01:19:56.666
In fact. if I had                 
 any say in this.

1711
01:19:56.708 --> 01:19:58.960
I would ask                       
 there be no recess.

1712
01:19:59.002 --> 01:20:02.130
[marbles continue clacking]       
                      [officer]     
                      Very well.

1713
01:20:03.048 --> 01:20:05.175
I simply want to ask.

1714
01:20:05.217 --> 01:20:08.553
if the performance                
 of these two officers             
 was so unspeakably bad.

1715
01:20:08.595 --> 01:20:10.388
why did you tolerate it?

1716
01:20:10.430 --> 01:20:13.475
Why didn't you beach them         
 or rotate them                    
 out of your command?

1717
01:20:15.852 --> 01:20:19.981
Well. this is gonna sound         
 strange to you. sir. but.

1718
01:20:20.023 --> 01:20:24.778
well. the truth is                
 I'm-I'm a softhearted man

1719
01:20:24.820 --> 01:20:26.822
and not many people               
 know that.

1720
01:20:26.863 --> 01:20:29.491
But I wanted to keep      
          them under-- under eye

1721
01:20:29.533 --> 01:20:32.619
to try and train them up.     
      make them good officers.

1722
01:20:32.661 --> 01:20:36.665
L-Last thing I wanted to do       
 was wreck their careers.

1723
01:20:36.706 --> 01:20:41.253
A concern they certainly          
 didn't share for me.              
 E-Either one of them.

1724
01:20:44.214 --> 01:20:46.508
Commander. on the morning         
 of the 18th of December.

1725
01:20:46.550 --> 01:20:48.385
the exact moment                  
 you were relieved of command.

1726
01:20:48.426 --> 01:20:50.011
was the   Caine                     
 in the last extremity?

1727
01:20:50.053 --> 01:20:52.806
Certainly not.            
 Was it in grave danger            
 at that moment?

1728
01:20:52.848 --> 01:20:55.517
Absolutely not.               
      I was in complete control     
      of the ship.

1729
01:20:55.559 --> 01:20:58.019
And did you inform                
 any of your other officers        
 of your intention

1730
01:20:58.061 --> 01:21:00.355
to change course.             
      come north at ten o'clock.

1731
01:21:00.397 --> 01:21:02.858
15 minutes                
          after Lieutenant Maryk    
          relieved you of command?

1732
01:21:02.899 --> 01:21:05.569
Yes. yes.                     
      I made that statement         
      and that was my intention.

1733
01:21:05.610 --> 01:21:09.447
Then Lieutenant Maryk's decision 
 to come north was not             
 a panicky. irrational blunder.

1734
01:21:09.489 --> 01:21:11.950
His panicky blunder   
              was relieving me.

1735
01:21:11.992 --> 01:21:14.536
I kept him from making    
          any disastrous mistakes   
          thereafter.

1736
01:21:14.578 --> 01:21:16.705
I wasn't trying       
              to vindicate myself.

1737
01:21:16.746 --> 01:21:20.333
Commander. have you seen          
 Lieutenant Maryk's medical log?

1738
01:21:20.375 --> 01:21:22.377
Yes. [chuckles]

1739
01:21:22.419 --> 01:21:26.006
Yes. I've read                
      that interesting document.    
      Yes. sir. I have.

1740
01:21:26.047 --> 01:21:29.050
Biggest conglomeration    
          of lies and distortions   
          and half-truths

1741
01:21:29.092 --> 01:21:30.635
I've ever seen.

1742
01:21:30.677 --> 01:21:32.345
But I'm extremely glad    
          that you've asked

1743
01:21:32.387 --> 01:21:35.181
'cause I wanna        
              get my side of it     
              all on the record.

1744
01:21:35.223 --> 01:21:36.641
Please.

1745
01:21:36.683 --> 01:21:39.060
Please give us your version       
 of any comments

1746
01:21:39.102 --> 01:21:41.062
factually related                 
 to episodes in the log.

1747
01:21:41.104 --> 01:21:43.732
Okay. well.                   
      starting right with           
      that strawberry business.

1748
01:21:43.773 --> 01:21:45.901
The real truth            
          is that I was betrayed.

1749
01:21:45.942 --> 01:21:48.028
d-double-crossed          
          by my executive officer

1750
01:21:48.069 --> 01:21:50.614
and this precious gentleman. 
      Mr. Keith.

1751
01:21:50.655 --> 01:21:52.574
who between them          
          corrupted my wardroom

1752
01:21:52.616 --> 01:21:54.618
so I was one man          
          against the whole ship.

1753
01:21:54.659 --> 01:21:56.578
No support                
          from my officers. okay?

1754
01:21:56.620 --> 01:21:59.039
[chuckles] Now. you take          
 that strawberry business.

1755
01:21:59.080 --> 01:22:03.460
Why. if that wasn't a case of     
 outright conspiracy to protect    
 a malefactor from justice.

1756
01:22:03.501 --> 01:22:05.712
Maryk carefully leaves out        
 the little fact

1757
01:22:05.754 --> 01:22:09.215
that I had conclusively proved    
 by a process of elimination

1758
01:22:09.257 --> 01:22:11.092
that someone                      
 had a key to the fridge.

1759
01:22:11.134 --> 01:22:14.596
Now. he says the messmen 
          ate the strawberries.

1760
01:22:14.638 --> 01:22:16.598
But if I wanted       
              to take the trouble.

1761
01:22:16.640 --> 01:22:19.476
I could prove to this court       
 categorically                     
 that they couldn't have.

1762
01:22:19.517 --> 01:22:21.436
I-It's the water business         
 all over again.

1763
01:22:21.478 --> 01:22:24.439
Like when the crew                
 was taking showers                
 seven times a day

1764
01:22:24.481 --> 01:22:28.234
and I tried to initiate           
 the simplest principles           
 of water conservation.

1765
01:22:28.276 --> 01:22:30.779
But. oh. no. Mr. Maryk.           
 the hero of the crew.

1766
01:22:30.820 --> 01:22:33.365
wanted to go right on             
 coddling them.

1767
01:22:33.406 --> 01:22:36.117
Well. you take                    
 that coffee business.

1768
01:22:36.159 --> 01:22:37.953
Well-- No.

1769
01:22:37.994 --> 01:22:39.788
[laughs]                          
 No. Excuse me.

1770
01:22:39.829 --> 01:22:42.248
Sorry. sir.

1771
01:22:42.290 --> 01:22:44.960
Strawberry thing first.           
 Okay.

1772
01:22:46.252 --> 01:22:48.463
Everything hinged                 
 on a thorough search              
 for the key.

1773
01:22:48.505 --> 01:22:52.133
and that's when Maryk             
 and. as usual. with help          
 from Mr. Keith. fudged it.

1774
01:22:52.175 --> 01:22:54.844
Went through                      
 a lot of phony motions.           
 didn't prove anything.

1775
01:22:54.886 --> 01:22:57.514
Like thinking                     
 that the burning out              
 of the coffee makers.

1776
01:22:57.555 --> 01:22:59.432
which were government property.

1777
01:22:59.474 --> 01:23:01.434
was some kind of joke.

1778
01:23:01.476 --> 01:23:03.979
And that was                      
 the attitude of everybody         
 from Maryk on down.

1779
01:23:04.020 --> 01:23:06.564
No-- No sense                     
 of responsibility.

1780
01:23:06.606 --> 01:23:09.234
And I kept emphasizing            
 over and over

1781
01:23:09.275 --> 01:23:12.654
that all of these things          
 were gonna have to be             
 accounted for.

1782
01:23:12.696 --> 01:23:14.823
[groans]                          
 It was a constant battle.

1783
01:23:14.864 --> 01:23:16.574
Always--                          
 Always the same thing.

1784
01:23:16.616 --> 01:23:19.369
Maryk and Keith                   
 undermining my authority.         
 always arguing.

1785
01:23:19.411 --> 01:23:23.832
Now. I wanted--                   
 I wanted to train Keith up        
 to be a good officer.

1786
01:23:23.873 --> 01:23:26.501
but I was stabbed                 
 in the back by--

1787
01:23:29.879 --> 01:23:31.423
Well...

1788
01:23:32.298 --> 01:23:34.009
[chuckles]

1789
01:23:34.050 --> 01:23:39.014
Well. I-- I think I've covered    
 that strawberry business.

1790
01:23:39.055 --> 01:23:41.141
And. oh. yes.                     
 the mess account business.

1791
01:23:41.182 --> 01:23:44.811
Well. I had to                    
 watch them like a hawk.           
 and believe me. I did.

1792
01:23:44.853 --> 01:23:47.355
[chuckles] Didn't sneak           
 any fast ones by me.

1793
01:23:47.397 --> 01:23:49.357
It wasn't for                 
      a lack of trying.

1794
01:23:49.399 --> 01:23:51.985
Instead of paying attention       
 to their accounts                 
 and their inventories.

1795
01:23:52.027 --> 01:23:53.862
which I would have to go          
 over again and again--

1796
01:23:53.903 --> 01:23:56.698
Always a few pennies short        
 or a couple dollars over.

1797
01:23:56.740 --> 01:24:01.578
But what do they care about       
 keeping accurate records?         
 Let the captain worry about it.

1798
01:24:01.619 --> 01:24:03.872
Well. by God. I did.

1799
01:24:03.913 --> 01:24:08.585
I-I defy anyone to find           
 a single wardroom mess statement 
 or ship service inventory

1800
01:24:08.626 --> 01:24:11.171
filed aboard the USS   Caine        
 while I was captain

1801
01:24:11.212 --> 01:24:13.631
that had a mistake                
 of a single. solitary cent.

1802
01:24:13.673 --> 01:24:18.136
And by that. I mean. I defy       
 a certified public accountant     
 to do it. Okay?

1803
01:24:18.178 --> 01:24:19.804
Well. what else?

1804
01:24:19.846 --> 01:24:21.973
[muttering]                       
 There's so much bullshit

1805
01:24:22.015 --> 01:24:25.018
in that precious log          
      of Mr. Maryk's.

1806
01:24:25.060 --> 01:24:28.521
Oh. yes! [laughs]                 
 Th-The movie business.

1807
01:24:28.563 --> 01:24:30.982
Okay.                             
 no respect for command.

1808
01:24:31.024 --> 01:24:33.443
Th-That was the whole trouble     
 with that ship.

1809
01:24:33.485 --> 01:24:37.322
The movie operator. who had       
 a disrespectful manner anyways.

1810
01:24:37.363 --> 01:24:41.409
started the movie                 
 without waiting for the arrival   
 of the commanding officer.

1811
01:24:41.451 --> 01:24:43.912
Out of that whole ship's crew.    
 officers and men.

1812
01:24:43.953 --> 01:24:48.750
did one person stand up           
 and call a halt or even notice    
 that the captain wasn't present?

1813
01:24:48.792 --> 01:24:51.920
I missed those movies             
 more than they did.

1814
01:24:52.962 --> 01:24:55.757
I banned them.                    
 and. by God. I'd do it again.

1815
01:24:55.799 --> 01:24:59.344
Wh-What was I supposed to do.     
 start issuing them all            
 letters of commendation

1816
01:24:59.385 --> 01:25:02.931
for this gratuitous insult        
 to the commanding officer?

1817
01:25:02.972 --> 01:25:04.099
[laughs]

1818
01:25:04.140 --> 01:25:06.601
It's not like                     
 I took it personal.

1819
01:25:06.643 --> 01:25:10.105
Uh. it's the principle.           
 The principle of respect          
 for the command.

1820
01:25:10.146 --> 01:25:13.942
That principle was dead           
 when I came aboard that ship      
 and I brought it to life.

1821
01:25:13.983 --> 01:25:15.985
And I nagged and I bitched        
 and I hollered.

1822
01:25:16.027 --> 01:25:18.613
and. by God. I made it stick      
 while I was captain!

1823
01:25:20.156 --> 01:25:22.492
Uh. and as I-- as I say.

1824
01:25:22.534 --> 01:25:24.786
it wasn't                         
 just the coffee makers.

1825
01:25:24.828 --> 01:25:26.496
It was a matter of respect.

1826
01:25:26.538 --> 01:25:29.082
When I ask a sailor a question.   
 I want a straight answer.

1827
01:25:29.124 --> 01:25:31.334
Nobody's gonna get away           
 with this shifty evasion.

1828
01:25:31.376 --> 01:25:34.420
if I have to hold                 
 a court of inquiry                
 for a week.

1829
01:25:34.462 --> 01:25:37.215
What do I care                    
 about strawberries?               
 It's a question of principle.

1830
01:25:37.257 --> 01:25:39.175
Stealing is stealing.

1831
01:25:39.759 --> 01:25:41.636
And on my ship--

1832
01:25:45.682 --> 01:25:49.644
Well. it's not like we got        
 a lot of nice treats anyway.

1833
01:25:49.686 --> 01:25:53.815
Uh... if we ever did              
 get something pleasant            
 once in a blue moon.

1834
01:25:53.857 --> 01:25:55.984
like--                            
 like strawberries. well.

1835
01:25:56.025 --> 01:25:59.070
it was outrageous that            
 I couldn't have a second helping 
